$ Python Webserver for CORS compatible HTTP requests

The following → development/languages/Python script (which I found → https://fpira.com/blog/2020/05/python-http-server-with-cors[on Francesco Pira's blog]) starts a
→ web/webserver that allows → web/webserver/CORS request.

This webserver takes zero, one (port, default: `8080`) or two (port and server address, default: `0.0.0.0`) parameters:
code {
$ ./websrv-cors.py
$ ./websrv-cors.py 7777            # listen on port 7777
$ ./websrv-cors.py 7777 localhost  # listen on port 7777, on localhost
code }

{ websrv-cors.py

  gh|scripts-and-utilities|/websrv-cors.py||

}

